search - find files by name
Executable: /bin/search.sh
Alias: search

DESCRIPTION
  Recursively searches the
  entire filesystem for files
  whose path contains the given
  string fragment.

USAGE
  search <name>

EXAMPLES
  search minux
  search .db

NOTES
  The search indexes the whole
  disk starting at / using
  minux.findfile(), which writes
  a temporary list to
  /temp/ls/files.ls.
  Results are printed one per
  line.

SEE ALSO
  ls    - list a directory
  find  - CraftOS file finder
